01:31.417 --> 01:33.254
<i>Reporting to you live from Lynwood County</i>

01:33.353 --> 01:36.142
<i>where a chilling scene
has been discovered by police.</i>

01:36.222 --> 01:39.813
<i>The bodies of four family members
were found inside early this morning</i>

01:39.893 --> 01:43.636
<i>in what police are describing
to be a brutal homicide.</i>

01:43.730 --> 01:46.939
<i>We are collaborating with various
law enforcement agencies</i>

01:47.033 --> 01:50.742
<i>on a possible connection to a previous
set of murders in Oakwood Glen.</i>

01:55.875 --> 01:59.584
<i>Dozens of miniature cameras
were found inside the property,</i>

01:59.879 --> 02:03.169
<i>hidden in household objects
such as smoke detectors,</i>

02:03.249 --> 02:05.126
<i>bookshelves and light fixtures.</i>

02:05.218 --> 02:09.223
<i>These killers are broadcasting
their crimes as a live feed.</i>

02:10.223 --> 02:11.845
<i>Viewers apparently had no idea</i>

02:11.925 --> 02:14.804
<i>that what they were watching
was happening in real life.</i>

02:14.928 --> 02:16.271
<i>I thought that it was fake.</i>

02:16.496 --> 02:18.135
<i>You just don't expect it to be real.</i>

02:18.231 --> 02:21.872
<i>I kind of feel sick to my stomach
about it, but it's still entertaining.</i>

02:22.068 --> 02:26.949
<i>It appears that these victims were given
the opportunities to defend themselves.</i>

02:29.342 --> 02:31.652
<i>This played out like
some kind of deadly game.</i>

02:33.413 --> 02:36.236
<i>The violence was kind of overwhelming...</i>

02:36.316 --> 02:37.886
- <i>Gruesome and...</i>
- <i>Graphic.</i>

02:37.984 --> 02:41.295
<i>But it was okay in the moment
because it was like a horror movie.</i>

02:41.454 --> 02:44.367
<i>I was rooting for them.
I really didn't want them to die.</i>

02:44.524 --> 02:48.748
<i>The whereabouts of a fifth family member
Marissa Vasquez are unknown tonight</i>

02:48.828 --> 02:51.751
<i>as authorities continue to search
for the young woman missing</i>

02:51.831 --> 02:53.640
<i>since the horrifying incident.</i>

02:55.168 --> 02:59.275
<i>Our working theory is that this feed
is being transmitted on a time delay.</i>

03:00.907 --> 03:03.096
<i>These killers are treating their broadcasts</i>

03:03.176 --> 03:05.098
<i>like a Hollywood horror movie,</i>

03:05.178 --> 03:07.488
<i>designed with one chilling purpose...</i>

03:09.382 --> 03:10.725
<i>...to entertain.</i>

03:12.552 --> 03:16.523
<i>The question that remains is,
will these killers strike again?</i>

03:16.623 --> 03:19.968
- <i>And if so...</i>
- <i>How will they select their victims?</i>

03:55.495 --> 03:56.599
<i>I keep having this...</i>

03:59.199 --> 04:00.610
<i>This nightmare.</i>

04:01.868 --> 04:03.905
<i>It starts the same every night.</i>

04:04.671 --> 04:05.911
<i>There's...</i>

04:07.207 --> 04:08.695
There's a storm outside.

04:08.775 --> 04:12.587
It's thunder and lightning and...

04:15.548 --> 04:17.221
I feel like I'm not alone.

04:17.784 --> 04:20.788
<i>Like someone's watching me.</i>

04:21.421 --> 04:25.028
<i>Someone is watching you? Who's watching you?</i>

04:26.526 --> 04:28.836
- <i>Her.</i>
- <i>Your mother?</i>

04:29.762 --> 04:31.332
<i>Well, at first I just...</i>

04:32.031 --> 04:33.533
<i>I feel her presence.</i>

04:33.800 --> 04:36.610
<i>But when the lightning flashes,
I can see her.</i>

04:37.003 --> 04:38.949
<i>She's laying on the kitchen table.</i>

04:41.241 --> 04:45.121
<i>And she's got a shroud over her.</i>

04:45.211 --> 04:47.033
<i>So what's happening in Jamie's world?</i>

04:47.113 --> 04:50.185
<i>And I can see all these bugs,</i>

04:51.351 --> 04:55.041
<i>these spiders and cockroaches,
and they're just...</i>

04:55.121 --> 04:56.376
<i>I'm fine.</i>

04:56.456 --> 04:59.130
<i>They're just eating away at her.</i>

05:01.361 --> 05:02.897
<i>Are you feeling scared?</i>

05:05.531 --> 05:06.669
<i>No.</i>

05:08.434 --> 05:11.847
<i>Those are very scary images.</i>

05:12.538 --> 05:16.782
<i>It's okay to be scared.
It's perfectly normal to be scared.</i>

05:17.777 --> 05:19.256
<i>Yeah.</i>

05:20.847 --> 05:26.695
<i>Sometimes letting yourself be
vulnerable makes you stronger.</i>

05:30.089 --> 05:34.094
<i>So do you think your father
has dealt with his grief well?</i>

05:34.994 --> 05:36.337
<i>No.</i>

05:36.562 --> 05:39.975
<i>He came home one day
with this new girlfriend.</i>

05:40.466 --> 05:42.139
<i>You must resent him for that.</i>

05:43.303 --> 05:46.512
<i>I don't resent him. I resent her.</i>

05:47.407 --> 05:49.887
<i>That's your stepmother, Olivia.</i>

05:50.376 --> 05:51.912
<i>How do you feel about Olivia?</i>

05:52.845 --> 05:54.586
<i>She's so different from my mom.</i>

05:55.982 --> 05:58.963
<i>I barely survived the first six months
of their marriage.</i>

06:01.321 --> 06:04.496
<i>Now, I gotta be stuck with her
on a whole 10-day vacation.</i>

07:15.661 --> 07:17.664
I told you, you should have peed
at the airport.

07:19.232 --> 07:20.575
I understand that.

07:28.975 --> 07:31.683
It's not gonna be a problem.
I'm gonna take care of it.

07:33.045 --> 07:34.701
Is there some maid you hired I'm unaware of?

07:34.781 --> 07:36.624
Coat on the rack,
suitcase out of the way. Come on.

07:36.716 --> 07:38.753
Wait, wait, wait. Steve.

07:39.185 --> 07:40.473
- Dad!
- Let me explain.

07:40.553 --> 07:42.999
- You're shouting.
- Let me explain.

07:43.389 --> 07:45.528
I'm gonna get you the money.
You have my word.

07:46.526 --> 07:48.199
The deposit should go through any day now.

07:48.961 --> 07:50.702
It's not like I'm trying to fuck you over!

07:52.298 --> 07:54.437
I'm not trying to give you the runaround.

07:54.700 --> 07:56.236
Look, I'm gonna work something out here.

08:06.078 --> 08:09.787
DJ, no food! It's almost 11:00.

08:12.018 --> 08:13.554
I know you can hear me.

08:29.669 --> 08:31.740
You've gotta be kidding me.

08:34.974 --> 08:36.919
Look, you don't have to threaten me.

08:37.477 --> 08:40.582
Expect a check tomorrow afternoon.
Two days at most.

08:42.280 --> 08:43.419
Okay, fine.

08:54.994 --> 08:58.237
- Is it a healthy snack at least?
- It's gluten-free.

08:58.698 --> 09:01.076
- Really?
- What?

09:03.202 --> 09:05.341
- How do you eat this?
- It's delicious.

09:11.811 --> 09:15.054
Something smells good.
You guys have a snack without me?

09:17.717 --> 09:20.129
What happened to the wallpaper in my room?

09:23.523 --> 09:24.968
Just feeling it out.

09:25.925 --> 09:27.529
We were gonna run it by you.

09:28.761 --> 09:30.206
But you didn't.

09:30.363 --> 09:32.240
And you just went into my room?

09:32.331 --> 09:34.277
Look, I really think
you're really going to like it.

09:34.367 --> 09:36.506
Look, I understand you're mad.

09:37.036 --> 09:38.991
Of course, we were gonna tell you first.

09:39.071 --> 09:43.019
We just thought that we'd
find something that you liked.

09:44.143 --> 09:47.716
Funny, because I don't remember
anybody ever having a problem

09:47.847 --> 09:50.919
with my wallpaper before. Right, DJ?

09:52.184 --> 09:55.461
- Right, DJ?
- Yeah. Totally.

09:56.022 --> 09:57.262
I mean,

09:57.356 --> 10:00.929
actually, that wallpaper is kind of creepy.

10:08.701 --> 10:11.773
Okay. This is really uncool.

10:11.871 --> 10:13.282
Jamie...

10:16.075 --> 10:19.648
You told me you were gonna ask her
before we tested the paint.

10:19.745 --> 10:22.168
I was going to,
and then I remembered how she reacted

10:22.248 --> 10:24.537
when I asked if I could throw out
her Harry Styles posters.

10:24.617 --> 10:26.028
This is not helping here.

10:26.452 --> 10:28.131
I mean, how'd she even see it?

11:33.319 --> 11:36.198
Hey, Josh, it's me. I've left you
like a thousand messages

11:36.288 --> 11:38.461
so just call me back when you get this.

11:53.639 --> 11:55.175
DJ!

11:56.642 --> 11:57.985
DJ!

11:59.178 --> 12:00.521
DJ!

12:01.781 --> 12:02.953
What?

12:03.449 --> 12:05.895
My charger, why did you take it?

12:06.786 --> 12:09.164
I don't know what you're talking about.
I have my own charger.

12:09.522 --> 12:12.059
- I don't believe you.
- Fine.

12:12.324 --> 12:13.530
Wait!

12:13.926 --> 12:16.736
So, you're not screwing with me?

12:16.829 --> 12:18.866
No. I'm being totally normal.

12:19.365 --> 12:20.753
You should try it sometime.

12:20.833 --> 12:23.837
Wait, Deej, wait.

12:25.404 --> 12:27.543
- I'm sorry.
- Whatever.

12:27.640 --> 12:29.051
Come on.

12:31.310 --> 12:32.755
It's just you and me, right?

12:35.347 --> 12:36.417
Sure.

12:38.284 --> 12:40.321
DJ, take out the trash!

14:23.689 --> 14:26.295
- Oh, my, God! Sorry. I'm sorry.
- Get out!

14:26.659 --> 14:28.605
- <i>Sorry.</i>
- <i>Get out of here!</i>

15:47.740 --> 15:48.878
Cool.

16:04.156 --> 16:06.136
You're gonna die!

16:06.525 --> 16:07.847
Matt!

16:07.927 --> 16:10.134
- I'm sorry, dude.
- You definitely frightened...

16:10.329 --> 16:13.640
So, that was too easy.
You were just like a sitting duck, man.

16:13.799 --> 16:15.938
- How you doing?
- I'm all right.

16:19.138 --> 16:20.617
You survive Florida, my man?

16:21.573 --> 16:25.077
Yeah. It was pretty boring. Hot as hell.

16:25.577 --> 16:27.784
I went to the beach, went to dinner.

16:27.880 --> 16:29.917
I'd rather be playing Xbox, but...

16:32.885 --> 16:34.364
It's on already?

16:34.486 --> 16:36.022
- Hell, yeah.
- Okay, I'm getting my revenge.

16:36.288 --> 16:38.911
- Let's do this.
- No, you can't push it like that.

16:38.991 --> 16:42.029
That is against the rules.
You can't do that, no!

16:42.127 --> 16:45.575
You can't score. DJ, I'm gonna kick your...

16:46.332 --> 16:48.676
- Hey, bro.
- You staying a while?

16:51.203 --> 16:52.512
I don't...

16:53.906 --> 16:56.819
Yeah, this... It's kind of a long story.

16:57.343 --> 17:00.518
Matt? It's 11:30 at night.

17:01.113 --> 17:02.854
Wait, why didn't you just call us at least?

17:03.482 --> 17:06.771
I was going to call, but Sheryl kind of

17:06.852 --> 17:10.276
accidentally deliberately
threw my cell phone in the toilet.

17:10.356 --> 17:12.393
But he's gonna be out of here in three days.

17:12.590 --> 17:14.400
Tops. Three days tops.

17:14.792 --> 17:17.865
Hi, Liv, how are you?
I'm good, thanks. Thanks for asking.

17:17.963 --> 17:20.034
- How you doin'?
- Oh, my God.

17:20.132 --> 17:22.169
No way. You're too hot for this guy.

17:22.267 --> 17:24.509
This is stupid. This just doesn't even work.

17:24.603 --> 17:25.707
- We got some pizza in the freezer.
- The two of you.

17:25.804 --> 17:27.593
- Go get some food.
- Okay.

17:27.673 --> 17:29.209
I'll set you up in the room.

17:53.165 --> 17:54.474
Coming!

17:55.968 --> 17:57.208
Yeah.

18:01.540 --> 18:04.521
- Hey, Killer. Hi.
- Hey, there.

18:06.078 --> 18:09.001
Now's not actually a good time to talk.

18:09.081 --> 18:10.720
No. No, no.

18:11.650 --> 18:13.493
You're not getting off that easy.

18:14.686 --> 18:17.257
You gotta give me something.
Come on, it's me.

18:18.857 --> 18:22.168
Catch me up.
I wanna know about your life. Go.

18:23.462 --> 18:25.635
Olivia's trying to destroy my life.

18:25.931 --> 18:29.572
Okay, first of all, refined sugars,
that's what's destroying your life.

18:29.701 --> 18:32.910
Second of all, Olivia is not scary at all.

18:33.205 --> 18:35.242
If anything, she's terrified of you.

18:36.575 --> 18:38.020
Why would she be afraid of me?

18:38.177 --> 18:41.625
'Cause you're a teenage girl.
Teenage girls are terrifying.

18:41.847 --> 18:44.794
One look from a teenage girl

18:44.883 --> 18:47.261
will send most men off... You just did it.

18:47.719 --> 18:49.130
You did the teenage girl look.

18:49.321 --> 18:50.960
I'm terrified right now.

18:51.557 --> 18:52.661
You see?

18:56.795 --> 18:58.001
I just feel like...

18:59.298 --> 19:02.575
Like I don't have a say in anything,
you know? And it stresses me out.

19:02.868 --> 19:06.816
It's good not to have a say in things.
You just gotta chill.

19:06.905 --> 19:09.977
Believe me, I know.
That's why I self-medicate.

19:12.344 --> 19:13.550
Really?

19:14.313 --> 19:16.691
It's for my glaucoma. You know that.

19:19.451 --> 19:21.226
All right, good talk, son.

19:21.920 --> 19:24.127
You gotta get out of this funk.

19:24.389 --> 19:25.766
Come here.

19:26.725 --> 19:27.965
Okay.

19:28.060 --> 19:31.303
Do your homework and eat more vegetables.

19:31.530 --> 19:34.443
And drink more water and exercise.

19:34.533 --> 19:36.069
That's what your uncle Matt says.

19:36.602 --> 19:38.241
It's really good. It's really good.

19:52.718 --> 19:55.096
He's my brother. What am I supposed to do?

20:03.162 --> 20:04.402
You tuck him in.

20:46.572 --> 20:49.712
<i>Hey, guys. Look at the camera.</i>

20:49.875 --> 20:51.946
- <i>Look up at the camera and smile.</i>
- What the...

20:52.611 --> 20:54.784
<i>What do you think? Is that a butterfly?</i>

20:54.880 --> 20:56.723
- <i>A butterfly!</i>
- <i>A butterfly?</i>

20:58.150 --> 20:59.925
<i>Did Mommy make a big butterfly, too?</i>

21:00.385 --> 21:01.694
<i>Great job too, Mommy.</i>

22:09.221 --> 22:12.862
<i>Hey, I got your texts. All 20,000 of them.</i>

22:12.958 --> 22:14.947
<i>I was worried that on your way home
from the airport</i>

22:15.027 --> 22:17.166
<i>you got trapped under a burning car.</i>

22:18.130 --> 22:21.111
- Can I ask you a question?
- <i>Yeah, go for it.</i>

22:25.404 --> 22:29.045
Do you see us staying together?

22:29.775 --> 22:32.187
I mean, like, past senior year.

22:35.280 --> 22:36.589
<i>Yeah.</i>

22:36.882 --> 22:39.124
<i>I mean, I think so. Do you?</i>

22:39.685 --> 22:40.823
Yeah.

22:44.623 --> 22:46.193
<i>Babe, what's going on?</i>

22:47.592 --> 22:49.595
Nothing. I don't want to talk about it.

22:49.828 --> 22:51.273
<i>Talk about what?</i>

23:10.615 --> 23:11.924
<i>Babe, what's going on?</i>

23:14.786 --> 23:16.026
Do you think

23:17.889 --> 23:20.012
even when people die

23:20.092 --> 23:22.265
they could still judge you for your mistakes?

23:23.295 --> 23:24.934
<i>Baby, are you talking about your mom?</i>

23:28.233 --> 23:29.678
<i>It's been six years.</i>

23:30.902 --> 23:32.905
<i>All right? What would she judge you for?</i>

23:34.973 --> 23:36.452
I gotta go.

23:37.576 --> 23:39.556
<i>Come on, I miss you,
and you're freaking me out.</i>

23:41.913 --> 23:45.122
<i>Talk to me. Like, did I do something?</i>

23:45.217 --> 23:47.026
<i>Did I screw up? Say something wrong?</i>

23:48.353 --> 23:51.163
No. No, it's not you. I just...

23:54.393 --> 23:56.498
- Yeah, I gotta go.
- <i>Jame.</i>

24:24.790 --> 24:27.737
Does she know I'm 35 grand deep?
No, I'd be a dead man.

24:29.261 --> 24:31.070
- Thirty five grand?
- Look, don't...

24:31.797 --> 24:33.743
Jesus, even the rich are poor.

24:35.133 --> 24:37.909
Here, man, it sounds like
you need this more than I do.

24:42.941 --> 24:45.319
Oh, God, it's like we're back in senior year.

24:46.878 --> 24:48.721
Where'd you get this shit anyway?

24:49.314 --> 24:51.351
Same guy we got it from in senior year.

24:52.117 --> 24:53.994
- No.
- No, I'm not kidding, man.

24:54.286 --> 24:56.163
- Dirk, he's a lifer.
- No.

24:56.555 --> 24:58.592
All right, I'm going to arrive
around the corner. Watch out.

24:58.957 --> 25:00.266
There's a guy right there.

25:02.461 --> 25:03.667
What the hell?

25:05.897 --> 25:07.433
Okay, sorry, I'm back, guys.

25:08.600 --> 25:11.342
Come on. That's bull crap.

25:20.278 --> 25:21.587
Jame?

25:24.816 --> 25:26.022
Yeah?

25:28.887 --> 25:30.594
Just wanted to see if you're okay.

25:33.758 --> 25:35.601
Yeah, I'm okay.

25:38.563 --> 25:40.065
Listen, I...

25:44.536 --> 25:47.210
We shouldn't have gone in your room
without your permission.

25:47.305 --> 25:48.477
It was stupid of me.

25:52.077 --> 25:54.523
I know this transition's been rough.

25:54.846 --> 25:57.588
And the last thing you need is someone
invading your privacy.

26:06.658 --> 26:08.797
All right. Good night.

26:15.300 --> 26:16.609
Night, Dad.

26:27.445 --> 26:30.085
Five more minutes, then the game
goes off and the teeth get brushed.

26:30.549 --> 26:32.529
- Can it be 10?
- Five.

26:45.297 --> 26:46.367
Shit.

26:49.401 --> 26:52.314
Maybe I've been trying to change too much.

26:53.238 --> 26:55.275
I'm just afraid
I'm never gonna connect with her.

26:56.107 --> 26:57.450
Stop it.

26:58.910 --> 27:00.719
You're just feeling each other out.

27:03.081 --> 27:05.755
Besides, you got lucky.

27:06.718 --> 27:08.527
You missed the zombie years.

27:10.589 --> 27:13.263
The piss, the shit,

27:13.725 --> 27:14.931
the puke.

27:16.461 --> 27:19.237
You took a shortcut
to the best parts of motherhood.

27:54.933 --> 27:55.934
No.

28:01.139 --> 28:03.244
What the fuck?

28:53.291 --> 28:54.998
What the fuck?

29:07.038 --> 29:08.517
Jesus!

29:09.841 --> 29:10.945
What?

29:16.347 --> 29:17.587
DJ?

30:14.205 --> 30:15.445
<i>It's started.</i>

31:48.366 --> 31:49.743
Two to three minutes.

31:50.735 --> 31:52.078
Yeah, okay.

32:55.900 --> 32:57.277
I'm in here!

33:43.915 --> 33:45.155
Hello?

34:33.164 --> 34:35.143
Did you hear that? Did you hear that?

34:38.136 --> 34:39.342
I got it.

34:56.554 --> 34:59.865
- What's going on?
- I don't know, I heard something.

35:00.158 --> 35:01.603
- Okay.
- What's going on?

35:06.631 --> 35:07.735
Matt,

35:09.333 --> 35:10.403
is that you?

35:13.571 --> 35:14.641
What was that sound?

35:18.543 --> 35:19.647
Matty?

35:22.780 --> 35:23.884
Matt?

35:33.257 --> 35:35.066
- Call the police.
- Okay.

35:37.195 --> 35:39.141
Dad, what was down there?

35:40.064 --> 35:41.338
What did you see?

35:42.600 --> 35:44.739
- What are you getting?
- It's okay.

35:45.970 --> 35:47.609
Just hang back, guys, okay?

35:57.949 --> 35:59.121
The phones are gone.

35:59.984 --> 36:02.240
Okay, get back in the bedroom
and lock the door. Now.

36:02.320 --> 36:04.061
Okay. Come on. Come on. Come on.

36:04.422 --> 36:06.766
Jamie! Jamie, come on!

36:07.992 --> 36:10.768
Stay up here. Listen to what your dad said.

37:17.628 --> 37:18.800
Hello?

37:26.637 --> 37:27.707
Matty?

37:34.245 --> 37:36.691
Matty, if this is you, it's not funny.

37:40.151 --> 37:41.186
Shit.

38:01.806 --> 38:02.910
Shit.

39:05.603 --> 39:06.980
Jesus Christ!

39:15.980 --> 39:17.118
What the fuck?

39:19.250 --> 39:22.026
Dad! Please come back upstairs.

39:22.119 --> 39:24.895
Jamie, go back upstairs.
Everything's gonna be okay.

39:25.122 --> 39:27.612
Dad, please. Please, come back upstairs.

39:27.692 --> 39:29.831
It's okay, sweetie. Get back up there.

39:40.171 --> 39:41.548
I can't see anything.

39:46.210 --> 39:47.587
What's going on down there?

39:53.284 --> 39:54.627
Dad...

40:25.649 --> 40:27.805
